# Design System Enforcement

When editing any component file, enforce these design system rules strictly. Every violation must be fixed before the change is complete.

---

## Color Token Map

### REQUIRED: Use Semantic Tokens

All colors must come from semantic CSS variable tokens. These are defined in `elephant-ai/apps/web/src/index.css` and automatically adapt for dark mode.

| Semantic purpose     | Tailwind class                        | CSS variable         | Light value              | Dark value               |
| -------------------- | ------------------------------------- | -------------------- | ------------------------ | ------------------------ |
| Page background      | `bg-background`                       | `--background`       | `hsl(0 0% 98%)`          | `hsl(222.2 84% 4.9%)`    |
| Primary text         | `text-foreground`                     | `--foreground`       | `hsl(222.2 84% 4.9%)`    | `hsl(210 40% 98%)`       |
| Brand primary        | `bg-primary` / `text-primary`         | `--primary`          | `hsl(240 86% 49%)`       | `hsl(240 86% 49%)`       |
| Primary button bg    | `bg-primary-dark`                     | `--primary-dark`     | `hsl(0 0% 9%)`           | `hsl(0 0% 98%)`          |
| Muted/secondary text | `text-muted-foreground`               | `--muted-foreground` | `hsl(0 0% 50%)`          | `hsl(215 20.2% 65.1%)`   |
| Subtle backgrounds   | `bg-secondary` / `bg-muted`           | `--secondary`        | `hsl(210 40% 96.1%)`     | `hsl(217.2 32.6% 17.5%)` |
| Card surfaces        | `bg-card`                             | `--card`             | `hsl(0 0% 100%)`         | `hsl(222.2 84% 4.9%)`    |
| Borders              | `border-border`                       | `--border`           | `hsl(214.3 31.8% 91.4%)` | `hsl(217.2 32.6% 17.5%)` |
| Error/delete         | `text-destructive` / `bg-destructive` | `--destructive`      | `red-600`                | `hsl(0 62.8% 30.6%)`     |
| Warning              | `text-warning` / `bg-warning`         | `--warning`          | `hsl(35 90% 50%)`        | same                     |
| Success              | `text-success` / `bg-success`         | `--success`          | `green-600`              | --                       |
| Focus rings          | `ring-ring`                           | `--ring`             | `hsl(240 86% 49%)`       | same                     |
| Links                | `text-hyperlink`                      | `--hyperlink`        | `hsl(221 83% 53%)`       | --                       |
| Inputs               | `bg-input-background`                 | `--input-background` | `hsl(0 0% 100%)`         | `hsl(222.2 84% 4.9%)`    |

### Status Color Patterns

```
Success: bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700 border-emerald-200
Warning: bg-amber-50 text-amber-700 border-amber-200
Error:   bg-rose-50 text-rose-700 border-rose-200
Info:    bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 border-blue-200
```

### Privacy Badge Colors

```
Public:  bg-privacy-public-bg text-privacy-public-text   (teal-50 / teal-700)
Private: bg-privacy-private-bg text-privacy-private-text (purple-50 / purple-600)
```

---

## FORBIDDEN Color Patterns

Reject and replace these immediately:

| Forbidden                 | Replacement                        |
| ------------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| `text-gray-500`           | `text-muted-foreground`            |
| `text-red-500` for errors | `text-destructive`                 |
| `bg-red-100` for error bg | `bg-destructive-light`             |
| `bg-white`                | `bg-card` or `bg-background`       |
| `text-black`              | `text-foreground`                  |
| `border-gray-200`         | `border-border`                    |
| `text-blue-600` for links | `text-hyperlink`                   |
| `text-[#anything]`        | Use the appropriate semantic token |
| `bg-[#anything]`          | Use the appropriate semantic token |
| `style={{ color: ... }}`  | Use Tailwind semantic classes      |

